In[9]:
def preprocess_text(text):
    text = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z0-9\s]', '', text)
    sentences = sent_tokenize(text)
    words = word_tokenize(text.lower())
    words_nostop = [w for w in words if w not in stop_words and w.isalpha()]
    stems = [stemmer.stem(w) for w in words_nostop]
    lemmas = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(w) for w in words_nostop]
    return {
        "sentences": sentences,
        "words": words,
        "words_nostop": words_nostop,
        "stems": stems,
        "lemmas": lemmas
    }

def jaccard_similarity(set1, set2):
    intersection = set1.intersection(set2)
    union = set1.union(set2)
    return round(len(intersection) / len(union), 3)

# Compute matrix
doc_names = list(processed.keys())
matrix = []
for name1 in doc_names:
    row = []
    for name2 in doc_names:
        sim = jaccard_similarity(set(processed[name1]['stems']), set(processed[name2]['stems']))
        row.append(sim)
    matrix.append(row)

# Display as heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.heatmap(matrix, annot=True, xticklabels=doc_names, yticklabels=doc_names, cmap='Blues')
plt.title("Jaccard Similarity Matrix")
plt.show()
